properties.title: Lake outside of Angkor Wat

Yeah, I know I put the horizon in the middle of the picture and that it is a huge NO and stuff... But frankly my dear... I don't give a d**mn, because I like it this way ;)

properties.title: Tuol Sleng
properties.description: vikkiness posted a photo: Phnom Penh, Vietnam - You're looking at the grounds of the Tuol Sleng Genocide Museum. This is where thousands of Vietnamese and foreigners were tortured during the regime of the Pol Pot.

properties.title: Bou Meng
properties.description: vikkiness posted a photo: He is one of the seven lucky survivors of the genocide. How did he survive? Well the Pol Pot was looking for an artist and guess what? Bou Meng can draw. See nobody knows who the Pol Pot was back then. So this guy drew the face of the Pol Pot without even knowing it.

properties.title: Weird fruit
properties.description: vikkiness posted a photo: Have you figured out how to eat this fruit? You have to take out those button-like circles and peel it. Then you eat the nut inside. Yep. It's a nut.

properties.title: Future Corona Commercial
properties.description: ca345 posted a photo: This hidden lounge outside Kep Village offers some of the most peaceful and unobstructed ocean views of any "tourist" town I have ever seen. You can order a crab dinner, hand-pick it out of the ocean trap, and enjoy for around $4 - Unbeatable!

properties.title: Silver Pagoda
properties.description: ca345 posted a photo: The Silver Pagoda in Phnom Penh has a simple design but is just as scenic as the Royal Palace. Spending a few minutes in the surrounding gardens, you will feel less-rushed and may be fortunate enough to chat it up with friendly monks looking to practice their English.

properties.title: Angkor Wat
properties.description: ca345 posted a photo: People line up everywhere to catch the sunrise over Angkor Wat but then often rush off to view other temples. There were very few tourists that managed to catch this breath-taking view of Angkor Wat from the back entrance. Green grass and unobstructed views make this one of the best places to see this crowded area.

properties.title: Four for one dollar
properties.description: Lonyl posted a photo: One of many young children selling their souvenirs and bracelets, sorting through her collection before attacking a new squad of tourists. These children often skip out of school to support their families, and they can be quite intrusive in their sales. Some of them know English quite well, others know more or less to say "Four for one dollar" and keep on "singing" that into your ear, until they get the sale through, or realize you not gonna buy.
